message:
Progress in the Fight Against Child Trafficking 
A 2016 study by the Center for Court Innovation estimated between 4,457 and 20,995 13- to 17-year-olds are involved in the sex trade in the United States.

data.description: The University of Maryland School of Social Work hosts statewide conference on sharing best practices to combat child trafficking.
data.title: Progress in the Fight Against Child Trafficking
